      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Historians largely reject the argument that the veto is a necessary feature, viewing it instead as a cynical compromise that prioritizes the self-interest of superpowers over global justice. While the veto prevented the immediate collapse of the organization during the Cold War, it fundamentally undermined its legitimacy and ability to act as a true global peacekeeper. Most scholars conclude that the system is broken because it was designed to protect the status quo of the powerful rather than to effectively solve international conflicts.",
      "source": "target",
